  "text": "Contributions. We introduce value-based Compressed Linear Algebra (CLA), [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] in which lightweight compression techniques are applied to matrices and then linear algebra operations are executed directly on the compressed representations. Figure 1 shows the goals of this approach: we want to widen the sweet spot for compression by achieving both (1) performance close to uncompressed in-memory operations, and (2) good compression ratios to fit larger datasets into memory. Our contributions include:",
